name: White-banded Swallow
rangeDescription: Eastern colombia to the guianas, southern venezuela, northern bolivia, and amazonian brazil
description: Small, unmistakable swallow of lowland rivers. Glossy black plumage, appearing metallic blue in good light, with bright white chest band is unique.

name: Fork-tailed Pygmy-Tyrant
rangeDescription: Southeastern brazil (rio de janeiro, southern minas gerais, and northeastern são paulo)
description: Tiny flycatcher with a very distinctive head pattern and tail. Best field marks are the cinnamon head and the long, forked white-tipped tail framed by a dark border.

name: Sichuan Jay
rangeDescription: Mountains of western china (southeastern qinghai, southwestern gansu, and northern sichuan)
description: Sooty jay with a dark head and a bright yellow bill. Unlike many other jays, tends to be quiet and unobtrusive.

name: Rufous-margined Antwren
rangeDescription: Northeastern brazil (bahia) southward to eastern paraguay, northeastern argentina, and southeastern brazil
description: A small antwren with a relatively long tail and bill. Restricted to southeastern Brazil.

name: Arctic Tern
rangeDescription: Arctic circumpolar; winters sub-antarctic and antarctic seas
description: Elegant seabird with extremely long wings and forked tail. Adults are pale gray with white cheek, black cap, and red bill and legs.
